		<td class="main_font" width="100%">


								
								
			<!-- Begin News/Information Section -->
				<table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
					<tr id="trmasthead">
						<td valign="middle" class="main_font" align="center">
							<font size="3"><b>&nbsp;</b></font>
					    </td>
					</tr>
					
					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=531995">Shar Vahl</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>battle claws for Beastlords</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    battle claws for Beastlords</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=532866"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:garyc77@earthlink.net">gary</a> | 
		                        12/13/2001 11:07:21 AM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">This quest starts after you complete the citizenship quest.  Talk to Poren, on the rightside of the guild hall, beastlord.  show him you slate.  he will give back the slate and give you a stiching bag, and a cloth wraps pattern. You need to train atleast 1 level in tailoring, I trained to the max, but i am not sure it helped.<BR>
     now go to the pit area, find one of the bridges leading out of the city, cross it, but instead of going on outside, climg down the rocks, into the area called the pit.  Every item you need can be found here, plus most of the tiems for the other city quests.<BR>
    First, you must kill the worms, to get their silk.  using the stiching bag, put two silks inot the bag, do not stack them, hit combine, and you will make threads.  Sometimes you fail, so keep trying. Put two threads in the bag, combine, and you get a bandage.  Put 3 bandages, and the pattern in the bag, combine, and you get cloth handwarps.  I failed 4 times, at this last part, so do not give up, or think you are doing it wrong.<BR>
    Now, darn, I thought i had this down, pat, at this point I can not remember for sure, but I think you have to go see Poren again, and he tells you what to do next.<BR>
    back to the pit again, you need, two YOUNG hopper claws.  Hunt Young hoppers only til you get two claws.  Put the two claws, and the clothwraps, into the stiching bag.  You still need iron fasteners.  Stay in the pit, and Kill scorpians, you need 4 scorpian legs.  after you have 4 legs, go to the armor store, it is near the raised pool of water.  just outside the side door, is a guy named karazz, show him your slate or talk to him about work, he will give you a box, and ask for 4 scorp legs.  Put the legs in the box he gives you and combine them.  give the box to him and he will give you a forged fastener.  now put the fastener, in your stiching bag, what already has two, young hopper claws, and the clothwraps you made in it and combine.  if you fail, like i did 7 times, you get the cloth handwarps back, if you succeed, you get two Khai Sha recruit claws.  6 dam 30 delay, Hand to hand.  they are beastlord, and kat race only.<BR>
<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
