			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Nothing much to add, just that for the combine of the dowel, fishoil soaked rag, sonic tendons, owlbear tendons, and kelp salt, your tailoring must be fairly high.  I have failed 7 times at the combine so far, once at 40ish skill, once at 45, 3 times at 50ish, and twice at 56 tailoring skill (which is as high as I can get making studded leather, and there's no silks to make cured silk in Luclin that I've seen).  I would recommend trying to get your tailoring well into the 60's before trying this, make bearskin potion bags or cured silk (not really an option for me since I'm on Sullon Zek, can't just roam around gathering items without getting pk'd ).  It can take quite a while to gather the quest items, especially the sonic wolf tendons (took me 8 hours to get one once, took 5 minutes another time), and it's very annoying to spend hours gathering these items just to destroy them in 1 second.<BR>
<BR>
Toxiss
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
