	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				After you have Collected the molars, You put them in the pouch Kaam gives you, hit combine and turn it in.  He then gives you A Set of Claw Mounts.  He proceeds on telling you to talk to Qua, and gets his tomes(he sells them, approx 5pp each) and then to talk to Jhimis(hes under Kery Miann, same building) for a Stretching Dowel.  Qua has 3 books, and 1 Weapon Assembly Kit(approx 5pp).  Kaam tells you to make a new set of Claws, and return to him the claws and the Apprentice cloak for your reward.<BR>
Jhimis doesnt sell the Stretching Dowel, its quested(like you are surprised?) You must get him 2 Owl Bear Claws, and your Apprentice Cloak.<BR>
After Reading the books, You find out You will need Reactive Sealant Soak, Sonic Wolf bane, Toughend Sinew Lashings, Porous Claws, Ceramic Claw Sleeve Set.  WWW.EQTRADERS.COM has these 3 book recipes on there site, Under Luclin Skills, so save yourself the 5pp a book.  Here is what the books say<BR>
<BR>
Sonic Wolf Bane Weapon: reactive sealant soak, sonic wolf bane (poison?), toughened sinew lashings, ceramic dagger sleeve*, porous dagger blade* (exception: Khati Sha, which needs porous claws &amp; ceramic claw sleeve set instead) - combine in the weapon assembly kit source: Wolf Bane Lore, Vol 1 <BR>
<BR>
Sonic Wolf Bane Poison: Poisonmaking: salass moss, tortoise saliva, sonic wolf blood, poison dart felt (from grunt shaman), mix in special acrylia mortar &amp; pestle (Vah Shir rogue item), then mix with posion vial and water source: Wolf Bane Lore, Vol 2 <BR>
<BR>
Toughened Sinew Lashings: Tailoring: owlbear tendons, sonic wolf tendons, stretching dowel, kelp salts and fish oil soaked rags - combine in large sewing kit source: Wolf Bane Lore, Vol 2 <BR>
<BR>
Reactive Sealant Soak: Brewing?: blackened salt crystals, sonic wolf brain, crystalized ygri root, digested night palm - brewed together in water and strained through a ceremonial strainer (Vah Shir shaman item) source: Wolf Bane Lore, Vol 2 <BR>
<BR>
Ceramic Sleeves: Pottery: clay made from ashes that remain after a grimling shaman has performed some dark ritual, flask of water, vial of owlbear bile, sonic wolf blood, black silt clay; sketch; quality firing sheet source: Wolf Bane Lore, Vol 2 <BR>
<BR>
Porous Dagger Blade: Smithing: ore made from white sand from the marshlands (near grunt camps), powered wolf claws, sonic wolf blood source: Wolf Bane Lore, Vol 3 <BR>
<BR>
Im am guessing that you substitute the Claws you have for the Porous Claws, and the Set of Claw Mounts for the Ceramic Sleeve Set.  OR  you make the porous Claws, and the Ceramic Sleeve Set, and make the Claw Weapons, then figure out how to attach the new claws, with the old ones and the Claw Mounts.<BR>
It also seems that we are going to need the other classes to help us on this quest, Tieing us all together.<BR>
NOTES:<BR>
After Killing enough Wolves for the molars, I only ran across the Tendions 1 time out of 30, it was dropped of a Sonic Wolf.<BR>
Ill be working on this quest until it is solved. So if you care to help, Send Duppot or Jarash a tell.  <BR>
<BR>
Jarash<BR>
Beastlord 13th Level<BR>
Quellious
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
