				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				In the Moor, Kill the hoppers, and get there tails It DOesnt take to long, they drop 1 out of every 8 approx.  Combine all 6 tails in the Bag you received from Rittah Purrik in the outpost(neg 850 pos 1980) And you receive an Note to give back to Kery Miann(Neg 300, Neg 350) in Vah Shar.  After she congratulates you, She gives you a box, and tell you to go find the glowing stone off the glowing mob in the caverns.  Head to the Paludal Caverns, Search for a Glowing Mob(cant think of there name exactlly, but you know its them when you see a massive amount of light giving off by the mob, as much as a greater lightstone, Also the mobs look the same as the Muck diggers, and Tunnelers.)  I got my Stone in the first try, put it and your cape from the previous part in the box, hit combine and return to Kery Miann.  Upon Returning the box, you gain exp, faction, a new cape, plus the whole zone gets to know your new title as &quot;Apprentice&quot;.  Sorry i dont have the cape stats off hand, but memory recalls 8ac, 2% tailoring, plus other stuff.  She Tells you to see Kaam Rahir.  He is located near the Kings Palace, in the building as you face the palace, to your Left.  You hand him Both your Claws, and he returns them to you, and a pouch.  He tells you that you must hunt wolf pups and get 2 molar fangs from them. Combine them in the bag, and hand in the bag and the 2 claws to him for new claws, that will be magic now.  Ive found the sonic pups in the moor, Still red to my lvl 13 Beastlord.  Ive killed many with my druid though.  Be Warned, the Sonic Wolves, Guardians, And another Sonic mob Are Light Blue con to a lvl 40. They also can keep up with Greater Wolfform.  Any of the wolves can drop the molar i am told.  WWW.EQATLAS.COM has a map of the Moor, and a location for the Wolf Caves.
